The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for iris segmentation, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep neural networks and data augmentation techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The mention of wearable headsets in the title suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and multimedia (cs.MM).
